This paper is about recommendation systems, which typically fall under the information retrieval (IR) sub-category of computer science. The paper proposes a new model for matrix factorisation that takes into account the criteria of novelty and explainability, which are important in the field of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also includes an initial user study, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (HC) and natural language processing (CL).
